main event: A civilian in Wilmington, Delaware reported seeing two unidentified aerial objects on October 5, 1966.
interesting points: The observer saw a white dot-like object, about the size of a pinhead, moving across the sky at a reasonable speed.
The white object changed color, going from bluish-white to greenish-white, then to reddish-orange.
As the red object approached the white object, the white object stopped and let the red object pass overhead.
The red object was described as a steady, fiery light that did not blink.
The sighting lasted for approximately 3-5 minutes.
sighted object: Two unidentified aerial objects, one white and one red
